records.addlTxt:
Status on the calendar for 16CF107, 16CM136, 17CF30, and 17CF41, as well as initial appearance in not-yet-filed matter. Defendant Trent J. Hanson in court, in custody, with attorney Lisa A McDougal. Prosecuting Atty Jennifer M. Harper appeared for State of Wisconsin. DA Harper states that the parties have an agreement for resolution of the four filed matters; notes that the State will not be filing charges in the matter tentatively on the calendar for an initial appearance today.

Def pleads no contest to the following counts:
16CF107, count 1, possession of narcotic drugs
16CM136, count 1, computer message - threat of injury
17CF30, count 4, disorderly conduct (with d.a. enhancer)
17CF41, counts 1 and 4, felony bail jumping and resisting/obstructing, respectively

Court's colloquy on pleas. Finding of guilty. Sentence as follows:

16CF107 - count 1 - sentence withheld for 3 years probation with conditions that def obey rules/regs; attend, pay for, and successfully complete any counseling, training or education ordered by the agent. Count 2 DRI.

16CM136 - 60 days jail with huber. 0 days credit. 1 set of costs.

17CF30 - 30 days jail, consecutive to time in 16CM136 - with huber and 7 days credit by stipulation. No costs.

17CF41 - count 1 - withheld for 3 years probation, concurrent and with same conditions as 16CF107. Count 4 - 90 days jail with huber, concurrent with jail time in 16CM136 and 17CF30. 7 days credit, by stipulation, applied to the jail time in this matter days jail. Counts 2 and 3 DRI. Costs waived.

Any posted bond to be returned to the poster as the costs ordered are in a case without $ posted to it and the $ poster in the other cases is not the def's so the Court is allowing it to be returned.
Status conference on June 2, 2017 at 01:30 pm.

16CF107, 17CF30, and 16CM136/status and 17CF41/adjourned initial, and one not-yet-filed matter. Defendant Trent J. Hanson in court with attorney Lisa A McDougal. Prosecuting Atty Jennifer M. Harper appeared for State of Wisconsin. Defense asks for prelim within 20 days in 17CF41; def is not in custody. Court directs prelims set for 6/2 n 17CF41 and 17CF30 and status that date/time in the other matters.  Status conference scheduled for June 2, 2017 at 01:30 pm.
